						mensa, thorusq[ue] breuis. 2. Eutrapelus. Officium vt faciat pars qua[e]q[ue] volubilis
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Axiophilus"/>
					<person name="Eutrapelus"/>
					<emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="Axiophilus"/>
					<emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="Eutrapelus"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						orbis, =
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						= Da purum, atq[ue] parum: Salue et I&auml;cche vale. 3. Enteleches. Officiu[m]	
						<!-- Continues onto facing page, right marign, Ha2.043v. -->
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Axiophilus. He drinks from the Nile and hastens away. The keen man is prepared, agile in body and mind;
				with a small table and bed. 2. Eutrapelus. His duty: that every part values the voluble world. <!-- Unclear. --> <!--JG: Don't the gens. qualify 'pars quaeque'?-->
				Give pure and equal: Greetings and farewell, wine. 3. Actualization. Its duty:
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		
